# Security Rules

## Authentication

- Server-side session checks on all protected routes.
- Never trust client-side auth state for authorization decisions.
- Password reset via Supabase Auth only.
- Consider MFA for admin users post-MVP.

## Authorization (Four Layers)

1. Middleware/route layout — session exists
2. Server action/handler — role check (`admin`, `super_admin`)
3. Service layer — entitlement check (plan, purchase, content rules)
4. Supabase RLS — user-owned data isolation

## Payments (Stripe)

- Never store card data.
- Verify `Stripe-Signature` on all webhooks.
- Store `provider_event_id` for idempotency.
- Grant access on webhook only — **not** on success redirect.
- Never trust client-submitted amounts or price IDs without DB lookup.
- `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` and `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`: server-only.

## Video (Mux)

- Signed playback only for paid content.
- Generate tokens only after `entitlementService` approves.
- Short-lived tokens (minutes, not hours).
- `MUX_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY`: server-only.
- Deny playback for: wrong plan, unpublished, processing, archived.

## File Downloads

- Private Supabase buckets only.
- Signed URLs after purchase ownership verified.
- Short expiry; never log signed URLs.
- Validate file type/size on admin upload.

## Webhooks

- Verify signatures (Stripe, Mux).
- Cron routes: require `CRON_SECRET` header.
- Return 200 quickly; enqueue heavy work.
- Log failures without exposing internals to provider.

## API & Forms

- Zod validate all inputs.
- Rate-limit public endpoints (`/api/leads/submit`).
- CSRF-safe mutations (Server Actions or same-origin POST).
- Generic error messages to users; detailed logs server-side.

## Secrets — Never in Client

- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`
- `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
- `MUX_TOKEN_SECRET`, `MUX_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY`
- `GHL_API_KEY`, `RESEND_API_KEY`
- `CRON_SECRET`

## Admin

- Role check in admin layout AND sensitive mutations.
- Log publish/unpublish and access rule changes.
- No casual `super_admin` grants.

## Logging — Never Log

Passwords, tokens, signing keys, full payment details, signed URLs, sensitive form data.

## OWASP Awareness

- XSS: sanitize rendered user content; React escapes by default.
- SQL injection: use Supabase parameterized queries only.
- IDOR: always scope queries to authenticated user ID server-side.
